properties.Title: Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A low pressure system from BC will pass through central Saskatchewan Friday night and then into Manitoba Saturday. A cold front trailing from this low will push through southwestern Saskatchewan tonight bringing very gusty northwest winds. For most areas gusts of 70 or 80 km/h should be expected tonight. Some localities are likely to receive wind gusts of 90 or 100 km/h this evening as the cold front passes through. Gusty northwest winds will spread throughout southern Saskatchewan by Saturday morning as the cold front sweeps through. This weather system will bring above normal temperatures today, but much colder temperatures Saturday. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Strong northwesterly winds are expected on Friday. A cold front over the North Coast will move southwards tonight and cross the Inner South Coast early Friday morning. Southerly winds of 30 to 60 km/h ahead of the cold front will shift to west to northwest 40 to 60 km/h behind the system with some gusts reaching 80 km/h over western sections of Metro Vancouver near the Strait of Georgia. Winds are expected to ease early Friday evening. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.
